/**
 * Role Definitions — per-project RBAC (beta.10 C6).
 *
 * Copy this file to roles.php. These are the FIXED built-in roles — there are no
 * custom roles (L8), so you should not need to edit this. Each role grants a set of
 * trust-coherent CATEGORIES (defined in categories.php), expanded to per-command at
 * load time by AuthManagement::getRoleCommands(). Enforcement:
 *   command -> category (categories.php) -> role grant (here) | global access rule.
 *
 * `rank` (viewer 1 … owner 6) drives the L9 "manages strictly below" hierarchy and
 * the F6 self-escalation guard (AuthManagement::canManageRole): a granter may only
 * assign/manage a role of STRICTLY LOWER rank than their own. There is NO superadmin
 * and NO '*' — `owner` (rank 6) is the top of each project. Per-project role
 * assignments live in each project's config/members.json, NOT here.
 *
 * Categories are cumulative up the tier (each role = all lower tiers' + its own),
 * listed explicitly for auditability (no inheritance logic). Engine config → PHP.
 */

return [
